You will work with the National Youth Sports Institute (NYSI) Youth Head Coaches and NSA coaches to design and deliver comprehensive plans dovetailing aspects of the youth coaching developmental systems and pathway(s). You will work with other partner agencies (and partners) to continue the development of coach pathway curriculum(s) in Singapore in coordination with other functional teams in NYSI using a transdisciplinary approach to attain high performance outcomes for youth sports ecosystem.

Requirements
•             Preferably a degree in Sports Coaching, Sports Science or related subject
•             At least 3 years of working experience in high performance sports environment with coaches and athletes, in particular with young athletes
•             Have worked with a variety of sports, including team and individual sports
•             Have a passion for sports (high performance aspect) with active involvement either as a national athlete, coach, participant or support crew